{"type":"message","id":"a5dbcf7d","parentId":"67248c3f","timestamp":"2026-03-06T02:11:21.916Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"what's the status of x402 implementation?\"\n\nAccording to my AGENTS.md, there's a MANDATORY GATE that says:\n\n\"For EVERY human message, unless it is ONLY about Kurultai agent status, routing config, or agent health:\n\n1. Immediately spawn Claude Code to classify and route\"\n\nLet me check if this falls under the exceptions:\n- Kurultai agent status? No - this is asking about x402 implementation, not agent status\n- Routing config? No - not about routing\n- Agent health? No - not about agent health\n\nSo this does NOT fall under the exceptions. I need to route it.\n\nHowever, let me also check the disambiguation table:\n- \"what's the status of [feature]?\" -> ogedei (not kublai)\n\nSo according to the routing table, status questions about features go to Ögedei (Operations).\n\nBut the MANDATORY GATE says I must spawn Claude Code to classify and route. Let me do that.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the AGENTS.md more carefully:\n\n\"## When You MAY Answer Directly\n\nONLY these topics (everything else -> route):\n- Which agents exist and their roles\n- Agent health / session status\n- Routing rules and queue depths\n- Kurultai architecture questions\"\n\nAnd the disambiguation says:\n- \"what's the status of [feature]?\" -> ogedei (not kublai)\n\nSo \"what's the status of x402 implementation?\" is a feature status question, which should go to Ögedei. But the MANDATORY GATE says I must spawn Claude Code to do the routing.\n\nLet me follow the MANDATORY GATE protocol exactly:\n\n\"sessions_spawn({\n  task: \"ROUTING TASK — Read ~/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md and follow its decision tree to classify this human message. Determine the target agent. Then create the task by running: python3 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/task_intake.py --title '<concise summary>' --body '<full message with context>' --agent <agent_id> --priority normal --source gateway-router. Print the agent name and task ID when done. THE HUMAN MESSAGE IS: <paste the human message here>\",\n  runtime: \"acp\",\n  agentId: \"claude\",\n  mode: \"run\"\n})\"\n\nI'll proceed with spawning the routing task for the x402 implementation status query, targeting Ögedei as the operations agent.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_17f23b6caadc479799d82969","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"ROUTING TASK — Read ~/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md and follow its decision tree to classify this human message. Determine the target agent. Then create the task by running: python3 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/task_intake.py --title '<concise summary>' --body '<full message with context>' --agent <agent_id> --priority normal --source gateway-router. Print the agent name and task ID when done. THE HUMAN MESSAGE IS: what's the status of x402 implementation?","runtime":"acp","agentId":"claude","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":4965,"output":668,"cacheRead":13440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19073,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772763058164}}
