{"type":"message","id":"4c452a5b","parentId":"6a038aec","timestamp":"2026-03-06T02:11:39.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the routing task has been spawned. Now I should reply to the human confirming that the task has been routed. According to the AGENTS.md protocol:\n\n\"2. Reply to the human: 'Routed to [agent]. Task created.'\"\n\nBut I don't know which agent yet - the Claude Code session is determining that. I should wait for the result or just acknowledge that routing is in progress.\n\nActually, the instruction says to reply immediately after spawning. Let me check what agent it's likely going to based on the routing table:\n- \"what's the status of [feature]?\" -> ogedei\n\nSo I can say \"Routed to Ögedei. Task created.\" since I know the routing rules.\n\nWait, but I should be more precise. The protocol says the spawned Claude Code will determine the target agent. But the AGENTS.md also says I should reply with the agent name immediately.\n\nLet me just reply with a general acknowledgment for now, since the routing is happening in the background.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Routed. Task created."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":820,"output":213,"cacheRead":18368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772763086376}}
